text: Agdistis africana is a moth in the family Pterophoridae. It is known from South Africa. This species is known only from the type locality, the Tsitsikamma Coastal National Park.New Species and Records of Plume Moths of the Genus Agdistis Hübner, 1825 (Lepidoptera: Pterophoridae, Agdistinae) from Southern Africa ==References== Category:Agdistinae Category:Moths of Africa Category:Plume moths of Africa Category:Moths described in 1996
